news.title: Secunderabad: Mahendra Hills building owners' high-rise hope gets fillip
news.para: A majority of the buildings in the area have seen no change in the past over five decades due to curbs on height and mandatory NoC from airport authorities.

news.title: Green nod for Ultratech Cement's two mining sites quashed
news.para: In its order dated February 21, the special bench of NGT ruled that the project fell under category ‘A’ and was beyond the purview of the State Environment Impact Assessment Authority (SEIAA) to grant environment clearances.

news.title: Over 86 hectare allotted in Aurangabad district for PMAY homes
news.para: As per the data submitted to the central government, out of 80,518 PMAY applicants in the district, only 355 have been allotted homes in the past five years.

news.title: Andhra Pradesh: Happy Nest home buyers issue legal notices to CRDA
news.para: According to the agreement entered with the CRDA, buyers have to pay 10 per cent of the total cost of the flat while the remaining has to be paid in tranches as construction progresses.

news.title: Maharashtra: Pay penalty to regularise housing membership on collector's land
news.para: This comes as a relief to at least 4,000 members of various housing societies on collector’s land whose membership had not been recognised by the collector.

news.title: Delhi HC seek LG, SDMC, police reply to PIL on illegal construction in Okhla Industrial area
news.para: The PIL committee of the high court had recommended that a July 7, 2017 letter by an individual be treated as a PIL in which he has complained over illegal construction and encroachment on public land in the industrial area.

news.title: New Delhi civic body to allot 120 flats to staff from next month
news.para: The seven-storey complex at Sector-7, Pushp Vihar in Saket will be named ‘Amrit Mahotsav Parisar’ and has been constructed over 1.6 acres for Rs 43.5 crore.

news.title: Builders welcome Rajasthan government's move to extend stamp duty rebate till March 2023
news.para: The developers are elated as announcement to extend the rebate of 2% stamp duty for units in multi-storey projects under 50 lakh till March 31, 2023, was made in the budget.

news.title: Seepage in flats, plaster peeling off: Residents in Noida seek better upkeep
news.para: Pointing out several incidents of plaster falls and damage to common areas such as stairways and balconies, the residents of these complexes now plan to meet the authority officials over the matter.

news.title: CIDCO extends registration deadline for mass housing scheme 2022
news.para: “CIDCO’s Mass Housing Scheme 2022 has received an overwhelming response. The deadline for submission of the applications has been extended to allow sufficient time for submission of documents and payment of the EMD amount. This will give an added window to the citizens who are willing to apply,” said Sanjay Mukherjee, Vice-Chairman and Managing Director, CIDCO.

news.title: Gurugram civic body to meet on delay in takeover of DLF colonies
news.para: Councillor Rama Rani Rathee said infrastructure in the colonies has not been upgraded even after the increase in floor area ratio (FAR) to four storeys.

news.title: Office space leasing to increase by 10-15% in 2022 : Experts
news.para: “Occupiers’ intention to expand is expected to exert downward pressure on vacancies in the coming years,” said Anshuman Magazine, chairman & CEO-India, South-East Asia, Middle East & Africa at CBRE.

news.title: No compliance to NGT norms, no OCs to builders: Noida authority
news.para: At a meeting called on Tuesday to review the progress made in an order passed by the NGT last year in a case related to the discharge of sewage by societies and its treatment, Noida CEO Ritu Maheshwari directed the Authority’s general manager (planning) to select a private environmental agency by March 15.

news.title: Shimao-guaranteed $174 million notes due March may not be redeemed - trustee
news.para: Regulatory curbs on borrowing have driven China's property sector into a liquidity crisis, with the struggles of Evergrande , the world's most indebted property firm, to repay its borrowings mirrored at several smaller rivals.

news.title: Max Estates lease out 1.05 lakh sq ft space in Delhi at around Rs 16 crore annual rent
news.para: "Average rental rate for Max House Phase 1 now stands at around Rs 125 per square feet per month," the statement said. Samsung India Electronics, Nykaa Fashion, Religare Enterprises, DSK Legal and Dhampur Sugar Mills are some of the key occupiers.
